      en: "Artistâ€™s Statement about this Painting This painting is a story of birth and continuity â€” a journey from earth to gold, from silence to awakening. Its green surface is not merely a color; it is the echo of lifeâ€™s beginning, the whisper of creation rising from stillness. The irregular textures and aged marks are the quiet scars of time â€” traces of endurance, transformation, and the passage of existence itself. At its heart, the paisley motif breathes like a living flame, curling upward from the soil of memory. No curve or line is accidental. Every twist carries the rhythm of centuries â€” the pulse of an ancient culture that has known both glory and sorrow. Here, the paisley is not just decoration; it is a spirit seeking to escape repetition, to fold into itself and be reborn. It is both seed and fire â€” the humility of earth and the majesty of light intertwined. The geometric border stands like the calm walls of a silent temple, holding the wild dance of organic forms within. This contrast between order and freedom mirrors life itself â€” the balance between what binds us and what allows us to grow. From the depths of aged green, golden light emerges, like a hidden sun filtering through the leaves of a forgotten forest. Beneath the layers of time, something still lives â€” something passed from generation to generation: faith, identity, and a devotion to beauty. This artwork carries the whisper of a nationâ€™s soul. The paisley â€” ancient, resilient, eternal â€” bends through time but never breaks. Its green speaks of life and renewal; its gold, of timeless brilliance. To look at this painting is to look into memory â€” where history breathes in color, and silence holds emotion. Every brushstroke is a meditation, a step beyond the surface into the unseen. In its stillness, the painting speaks. It invites the viewer to pause, to breathe, and to listen â€” for somewhere within its green and golden quiet, beauty still lives, and it will never fade." 
