      en: "Artistâ€™s Statement about this Painting In this artwork, patterns and letters intertwine, as if time itself has lost its way within this sacred circle. At the heart lies a cluster of Kufic lettersâ€”echoes from an ancient civilization that still breathes within our souls. Each letter is a body of light and shadow, and every space between them is a pause of thought and presence. These letters do not speak, yet they are heard â€” their silence resounds with eternity. The borders bloom like a garden of repetition and rhythm. The swirling forms balance control and freedom; the earthy reds, turquoise, and olive tones recall the essence of soil, sky, and blood â€” the eternal triad of Persian spirit. Amid this dance of forms, a golden glow emerges â€” not from metal, but from the essence of meaning itself. This piece is not merely decorative â€” it is a journey into identity. The more the viewer gazes, the less they â€œseeâ€ and the more they enter. The colors and lines pull the mind inward, layer by layer, until the viewer becomes part of the painting itself. Here, the artist has painted not just with the hand, but with the soul. Each brushstroke is a testimony of faith in beauty and meaning â€” a bridge between sacred geometry and poetic chaos, between matter and spirit. And finally, silence. The silence left between the shapes speaks louder than the pigments themselves. This painting has neither beginning nor end â€” it is like a prayer, circling endlessly, whispering the secret of eternity." 
