      en: "Artistâ€™s Statement about this Painting In this new creation, I wanted to let silence speak. A silence made not of emptiness, but of power â€” the kind that hums beneath the surface of stillness. The deep black is not absence, itâ€™s depth. Itâ€™s the unknown, the hidden heart of existence where everything begins and ends. Upon it, the golden fragments rise like whispers of light fighting their way through the shadows â€” small, imperfect, yet alive with purpose. These golden shapes are not random. Each one carries its own story, its own memory of struggle and rebirth. They are pieces of dreams once broken, now reborn in brilliance. Together they form a river of gold, a pulse of life moving across darkness â€” as if the night itself has chosen to reveal the treasure it hides. When I painted this, I thought about how beauty is never clean or perfect; itâ€™s carved from resistance, from chaos, from loss. Gold only glows because of the black that surrounds it. That contrast â€” that tension â€” is what makes life extraordinary. The painting reminds us that even when we walk through darkness, we are still carrying something radiant inside us. If you stand before it long enough, you may begin to feel its rhythm â€” the slow breathing of the unknown, the quiet strength of what cannot be destroyed. This is not just a painting; itâ€™s a conversation between shadow and light, a silent rebellion of hope. Because somewhere in every darkness, gold is still breathing." 
